<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
If they don't do anything else, it would be nice if they gave pets the ability to act like a tank for us.  Intercept, guard, block.  It was brought up in another post and I thought it was a good idea.  <P>Pets as of now are an annoyance (unless you are inside a keep with an underhill compatriot nuking you through walls).  <P>Aggressive = How defend is now.  The pet attacks anything that attacks you.  <P>Defend = the pet stays by your side and intercepts, guards, protects - will not go on the offensive until you tell him to go aggressive.<P>Passive - why would we want a passive pet?  Get rid of this button.<P>Stay - Aggressive = use ranged attacks<BR>Follow - Aggressive = /stick to target until dead<P>Stay and Follow = Defend is the same thing as defend.<P>Another thought would be the ability to control the pet like it is us.  We get all the abilities of the mob we charmed, but our sorcerer body is just standing there.  If the body is killed, we automatically release.  If the pet is killed, we return to our body.<P>Imagine taking over an isolationist scout and scouting  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">  Or a cleric and healing.  Of course, if you are doing that in PvE then you can't mez, so there are drawbacks.<P>--------------------<P>Malachai Mindbender<BR>Sorcerer of Avalon<BR>Guinivere
